-- EADS CEO says to review strategy after BAE merger talks ended
-- 
-- Wed Oct 10, 2012 3:15pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/10/10/us-eads-strategy-idUSBRE8991HP20121010

 

 PARIS  (Reuters) - EADS Chief Executive Tom Enders said in a letter to employees that the aerospace group wished to review its strategy and defense activities in particular after the end of its merger talks with BAE Systems. 
 "We will now take the time to clearly draw a number of lessons from this experience. We will need to review our Group strategy and defense activities in particular," Enders said in the letter which was sent to employees on Wednesday. (Reporting by  Astrid Wendlandt , editing by Leigh Thomas)